history.content:
I've been posting a lot of speaker events here but here's something a little different this time: a resume workshop + feedback session! Here's the blurb:

Want to avoid the common pitfalls seen on most resumes? Seeking concrete ways to sharpen your resume before the semester starts? Looking for an excuse to avoid yet another Zoom birthday party?

Join us on Friday (August 14th) at 4pm PT as Florian's founder Emon Motamedi leads a workshop on crafting the perfect resume.

We will be giving live feedback on certain sections of pre-chosen resumes during the session. Students who are open to receiving feedback can email their resume to students@joinflorian.com (names will be redacted).

Register here: https://zoom.us/meeting/register/tJMvf-Cprj4iEtXXhQczlTuIb2SOrdzFmcoF

This event is part of Florian's weekly event series. Florian is a community of Cal alumni helping students pay for school without loans and get ahead in their careers. You can learn more at joinflorian.com.
history.subject: Resume Feedback + Workshop Event
